*Morocco's pilot project uses floating solar panels* to reduce water evaporation and produce green energy amid a severe drought.
*The floating solar system* can cut evaporation by about 30%, helping conserve water resources.
*The project aims* to generate 13 MW of electricity for the Tanger Med port complex, with plans to expand further.

